In our current setup, if `/project` is indeed a bind mount with an ext4 type, it might cause our derivation to point to the wrong entry, but since the operation ran successfully, maybe full isolation isn’t active. I'm checking that in the internal execution wrapper, extension calls are made only if `fs_mode_writable` is true, and we would fail if there's a wrong filesystem type.
