I'm looking into the smoke scripts in the planning pack that likely run `substrate world doctor` and `substrate --world`. If the runner's world-agent isn't updated to the latest commit, smoke tests might fail, which could be a problem. I wonder if the CI smoke runners are set up to use a compatible world-agent service? It seems crucial that not only the code changes are in sync, but also that the binaries stay compatible. Let's explore this further and check the specifics in the relevant documentation.
