I'm considering the complexity of the world-agent service, which might be activated by a socket and run through systemd to use the version stored on disk. On CI runners, it might be updated regularly, but PR-level tests would use what's already there. To ensure the updated world-agent binary is in play, it's possible the self-hosted runner uses an in-repo world-agent binary instead. I need to double-check if this aligns with how the `substrate --world` command interacts with the service and whether smoke scripts build and start it during tests.
