It seems that the world-agent service on their runners might already be patched not to remount the overlay as read-only when full isolation is in place, using landlock for enforcement. This could mean that my local environment is outdated and needs an update. The specification indicates that allowlisted writes should succeed unless denied by landlock, suggesting the mount semantics aren't the issue. However, since our repo script does remount the overlay to read-only, this might need fixing. Still, the EPERM error we're seeing could relate to landlock, even with the helper disabled.
